&lt;p&gt;We’re currently looking for a Channel Marketing Manager who will take a key role on our United States location-neutral team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This individual will report to the Head of Marketing and work in close partnership with the Partnerships team. They will be the engine behind channel marketing execution by building and running the programs that keep reseller partners and their frontline reps informed, engaged, and equipped to sell SwipeSimple. In this role, we value someone who is a strong storyteller and clear communicator, highly organized with an eye for detail, and comfortable owning the end-to-end execution of webinars, events, and growing a newsletter.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Partner Account Co-Marketing&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as the dedicated marketing contact for assigned reseller partner accounts, building working relationships with their marketing and sales counterparts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with the Partnerships sales team to understand each account&#39;s goals and capacity, then propose and develop tailored co-marketing campaigns, promotions, and joint programs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own execution from brief through delivery — co-branded emails, promotional offers, custom collateral, and event-tied activations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support preparation of Quarterly Business Reviews for major partner accounts, contributing marketing performance data and forward-looking program recommendations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Track and report on co-marketing program performance by account, identifying what is working and bringing new ideas to the table&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Events &amp;amp; Trade Shows&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Plan and execute logistics for 4–6 regional and national trade shows per year, including NEAA, SEAA, MWAA, WSAA, and ETA TRANSACT and potentially partner conferences, covering booth design, registration, badge management, branded giveaways, printed collateral, shipping coordination, and on-site setup&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead involvement in ETA TRANSACT end-to-end as the company&#39;s largest annual industry event, including vendor management for booth build and materials, branded giveaways, partner outreach, and trade show activation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support planning and execution of the annual&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.cardflight.com/conference-2026&quot;&gt; CardFlight Conference&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage relationships with booth vendors, print vendors, and swag suppliers; coordinate budget submissions and track spend against allocated budgets&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Write and publish LinkedIn content before, during, and after each show; source and post images from the floor&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Webinar Programs&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own the full content lifecycle of SwipeSimple webinars for reseller and frontline audiences, selecting topics in partnership with the Partnerships team, building the narrative arc, and developing the slide deck&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Write and sequence the pre-webinar email campaign to drive registrations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Configure webinar logistics in Zoom, including panelist setup, Q&amp;amp;A, cloud recording, and automatic reminder emails to registrants&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Distribute post-webinar follow-up to attendees and registrants, including the recording, slide deck, and any resources referenced during the session&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Pull and deliver the registration list and Q&amp;amp;A report to the Partnerships team after each session&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Email Marketing&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own the Frontline Nurture email program, a monthly send to front-line sales reps at reseller partner accounts covering product news, upcoming webinars, and selling reso

&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who We Are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are a leading payments technology company that empowers small businesses across the United States to accept payments seamlessly through our flagship product, SwipeSimple. We distribute our solutions primarily through a robust network of hundreds of merchant acquirers and independent sales organizations (ISOs), who in turn onboard thousands of merchants onto the SwipeSimple platform each month.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are backed by private equity, including WestView Capital Partners, and are at an exciting inflection point in our growth journey.&amp;nbsp; We have a strong foundation of profitable recurring revenue today, and are focused on scaling over the next three to four years through optimizing our core channel, accelerating our direct-to-merchant offering, expanding value-added services, and selectively entering new markets.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To achieve this growth, we are hiring our first-ever Chief Revenue Officer—a seasoned revenue leader who will own the full commercial engine of the business and drive CardFlight into its next chapter.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Position&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As CardFlight’s first Chief Revenue Officer, you will be the senior-most commercial leader in the organization, reporting directly to the CEO. You will own all revenue-generating functions—channel sales, direct-to-merchant sales, marketing, and the app marketplace—and lead a team of approximately 15 professionals across these disciplines.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is both a strategic and hands-on role. You will be expected to set the vision and long-term direction for CardFlight’s go-to-market function while also being deeply engaged in day-to-day execution—coaching teams, refining processes, and driving results directly. This is not a role for a purely conceptual executive; we are looking for a player-coach who leads from the front.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Channel Sales — Acquirer &amp;amp; ISO Network&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own and grow the core ISO and merchant acquirer channel, which is CardFlight’s primary distribution engine.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and execute a strategy to reignite growth in a mature channel through fresh approaches to partner recruitment, enablement, and incentive structures.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deepen relationships with existing acquirer and ISO partners while identifying and onboarding high-potential new partners.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as a senior commercial point of contact for CardFlight’s most strategic channel relationships.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Direct-to-Merchant Sales — SwipeSimple Connect&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Scale SwipeSimple Connect, our early-stage direct-to-merchant sales channel, from its currently early-stage revenue base into a meaningful and growing contributor to total company revenue.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and refine the sales motion, tooling, and team structure required to efficiently acquire merchants directly at scale.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify and pursue referral partnerships and other top-of-funnel channels that accelerate direct merchant acquisition.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Marketing&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead CardFlight’s marketing function, including demand generation, performance marketing, referral partnerships, product marketing, and brand.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and optimize top-of-funnel programs that drive both channel partner recruitment and direct merchant sign-ups.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure tight alignment between marketing and sales, with clear ownership of funnel stages and handoff processes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;App Marketplace &amp;amp; Value-Added Services&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive cross-s

&lt;p&gt;We&#39;re currently looking for a Payments Product Manager who will take a key role on our United States location-neutral team. You&#39;ll serve as CardFlight&#39;s payments domain expert. Bringing leadership, expertise, and experience across transaction networks and methods, processor integrations and certifications, compliance mandates, card brand relationships, and emerging payment standards, while serving as the connective tissue among the payments team, engineering, and the broader product organization.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You’ll interpret product strategy, technical specifications and translate complex requirements into engineering-ready stories. This is a product management role at its core — you will own the strategy, requirements, and roadmap for our payments infrastructure. The nature of payments integrations and certifications means a meaningful portion of your time also involves project-level execution, but the job is defined by product thinking, not task coordination.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this role, we value someone who brings deep payments expertise and a genuine customer-centric product mindset, combined with deep understanding of the context and constraints in payment transaction processing, and a pragmatism and solution-oriented mindset to create and ship elegant solutions despite lots of complexity below the surface.&amp;nbsp; You thrive in technical ambiguity, operate with a high degree of self-sufficiency, and understand that in payments, the details matter as much as the strategy.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Payments Strategy &amp;amp; Certification Ownership&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Providing product thought leadership on how all transactional components of our product function, how that maps to processor integrations, our roadmap for end-to-end certification processes, while working alongside the certification team on execution.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Managing processor integration and certification processes end-to-end, from intake paperwork through testing and delivery, including negotiating scope and requirements with certification analysts at major processors.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serving as the primary point of contact with processors and card brands for compliance matters, emerging standards, and production issues, with the communication skills and relationship-building discipline to represent CardFlight effectively in high-stakes technical conversations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Reviewing card brand compliance bulletins and emerging payments standards, developing a pragmatic point of view on where the product needs to evolve, surfacing and actioning those recommendations proactively.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Acting as CardFlight&#39;s internal expert on topics like emerging payment methods and standards, EMV kernels, certification intake requirements, and processor integration architecture, helping the broader team build knowledge.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Managing many concurrent workstreams across multiple active certifications and processor integrations simultaneously without losing attention to detail.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Technical Requirements &amp;amp; Spec Interpretation&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Reading and interpreting raw specification documents from card brands and processors, and translating them into clear, engineering-ready requirements, user stories, and Product Requirements Documents without requiring them to be pre-interpreted by someone else.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identifying compliance obligations from standards bodies like EMVCo and PCI-DSS, card brand rules and processor integration specs, and proactively surfacing requirements before they become production issues.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assessing how new user-facing features impact processor integrations and certification requirements, and flagging those dependencies early in the

&lt;p&gt;We’re currently looking for a Product Manager who will take a key role on our United States location-neutral team.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;This individual will work alongside four other team members, while also collaborating cross-functionally with teams across the organization. They will translate customer needs and business goals into clearly articulated requirements, driving the development of products that acquire and retain merchants.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;In this role, we value someone who leads with a clear understanding of the problem before reaching for the solution, operates with a high degree of self-sufficiency in a lean team environment, and brings enough technical and business depth to connect customer needs, partner constraints, and engineering execution into a clear path forward.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Discovery &amp;amp; Prioritization&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conducting merchant interviews and participating in reseller calls to understand pain points firsthand, while also synthesizing support tickets, feature requests, Pendo data, and usage metrics to build a complete picture of customer and partner needs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Synthesizing discovery inputs into clear problem statements that align the team around what is being solved and why before solutioning begins.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partnering with the broader product team to prioritize what gets built and when, with decisions weighted heavily toward features that drive revenue growth.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Roadmap Stewardship &amp;amp; Launch Readiness&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintaining and executing against a product roadmap that balances new features, platform improvements, and technical debt.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Clearly communicating the reasoning behind roadmap decisions to engineering, marketing, operations, and partner teams so everyone understands not just what is being built but why.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Owning launch readiness by coordinating across teams to ensure messaging, documentation, partner communications, and engineering work are all aligned and complete before a feature ships.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Data-Informed Decision Making &amp;amp; Requirements&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Using product analytics tools to analyze feature adoption and user behavior, and translating that data into a clear narrative that builds the case for what should be built, changed, or deprioritized.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Translating customer and business needs into clear specs, user stories, or PRDs that engineering can build from.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cross-Functional Collaboration&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Embedded in the engineering team&#39;s daily rhythm, attending standups, refinements, and sprint planning, and reviewing completed work to ensure it meets the intended product outcome before release.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partnering with marketing to review content, walk through feature use cases, and ensure messaging accurately reflects what the product is designed to do.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working with operations to share product requirements, review documentation, and train the team on how new features work so they can effectively support merchants after launch.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborating with the partnership team to gather and incorporate feedback from resellers and acquirers, and to coordinate release timing and communications so external partners are informed and prepared for every product change.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Bring to the Table&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2-8 years of product management experience shipping in-house software.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A demonstrated track record of shipping software product

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Senior Account Executive – Inside Sales&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;CardFlight | SwipeSimple Connect&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;Greater Phoenix, AZ (Remote) | OTE $120,000+&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Small businesses are the backbone of local economies — and you&#39;ll be the person helping them modernize how they get paid. As a Senior Account Executive at CardFlight, you&#39;ll sell SwipeSimple Connect, our CRM and payment processing solution, directly to small business owners who need it. Our current Senior AEs consistently exceed their targets, and the earning potential reflects that.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;OTE: $120,000+, with uncapped upside for top performers.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location:&lt;/strong&gt; Greater Phoenix, AZ. Primarily remote.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You&#39;ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own the full sales cycle — from cold outreach to close. No handoffs, no committee decisions. You prospect, you pitch, you close.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and work a pipeline of small business owners through cold calling, email, and digital outreach.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Run consultative demos that show SMB owners exactly how SwipeSimple Connect improves their operations and bottom line.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Keep your CRM tight and your forecast accurate.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with marketing and product teams to sharpen your pitch and stay ahead of the market.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;What You&#39;ll Bring&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3–5+ years in sales, ideally selling to SMBs in SaaS, fintech, or payments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A track record of consistently hitting and exceeding quota&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfort and confidence selling directly to small business owners&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong closing skills and a bias toward action&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;CRM proficiency and the ability to pick up new tools quickly&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;The Opportunity&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;CardFlight&#39;s SwipeSimple platform is already trusted by 125,000+ small businesses nationwide. You&#39;ll be selling a proven product to a market that needs it, with a compensation structure designed to reward performance. We offer a 3-month ramp-up plan, a clear path to advancement, and company equity so your growth is tied to ours.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;Benefits&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Remote-first with home-office stipend&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comprehensive health benefits&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stock options&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Learning &amp;amp; development culture, team events, and Lunch &amp;amp; Learns&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
